98
00:04:52,181 --> 00:04:53,930
because they were very proud of the brand,

99
00:04:53,930 --> 00:04:55,721
had been very successful in other markets--

100
00:04:55,721 --> 00:04:57,520
would be very well known in Vancouver.

101
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:58,835
That was one hypothesis.

102
00:04:58,835 --> 00:05:00,710
A second hypothesis, they thought that people

103
00:05:00,710 --> 00:05:04,580
would be pretty excited about the way they did their marketing and promotion.

104
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:09,160
Specifically, how they communicated to the people in the marketplace.

105
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:11,370
And the third thing is they thought that they

106
00:05:11,370 --> 00:05:14,190
really quite knew what types of consumers

