138
00:06:58,870 --> 00:07:02,250
was that wealthier consumers-- consumers that

139
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:06,030
were earning a fair amount of money annually in their households,

140
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:09,700
well into the six figures-- would be the primary customer.

141
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:11,920
That this is the group of people-- and we'll

142
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:14,315
talk next class on the notion of segmentation--

143
00:07:14,315 --> 00:07:16,440
but this would be the group of people that would be

144
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:20,460
really excited to buy these products.

145
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:23,800
They were shocked though when we found that there was actually

146
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:27,210
two groups of people when you looked at income

147
00:07:27,210 --> 00:07:28,640
that wanted to buy these products.

148
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:30,180
Yes, the wealthy.

149
00:07:30,180 --> 00:07:36,520
But also, people that were only making $20,000 to $30,000 or so a year.

150
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:40,240
Why did they want to buy this high end luxury product?

151
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:44,320
