152
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:48,530
And it's the idea that sometimes as consumers, there's

153
00:07:48,530 --> 00:07:51,830
certain products that you really want that you can't afford,

154
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,730
but you'll save up for them.

155
00:07:53,730 --> 00:07:59,030
And you'll forgo other things because you want that expensive thing.

156
00:07:59,030 --> 00:08:01,450
Some people, that's vacations.

157
00:08:01,450 --> 00:08:03,200
Some people, that's cars.

158
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,020
Some people, that's a piece of art.

159
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:09,660
And for a good chunk of consumers, it was actually this high end fashion

160
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:10,800
brand.

161
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:15,120
That they wanted to buy, and they would be a lot cheaper perhaps

162
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:18,310
for a month on their other expenses.

163
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:21,760
Now the company was obviously interested and surprised to learn

164
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:25,010
about these bits of information.

165
00:08:25,010 --> 00:08:29,440
And why it was important was it empowered them as an organization

166
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:33,520
when they opened their store to know more about the consumer,

167
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:37,440
understand how to better promote their product,

168
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:40,309
what the pricing structure would be, what they needed

169
00:08:40,309 --> 00:08:42,450
to do with respect to their brand.

170
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:47,670
The information empowered the organization to do a much better job,

171
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:50,890
and hopefully for them be successful.

